"**Comparison of Policies: Namal Rajapaksa vs. Dilith Jayaweera**\n\n| **Policy Area** | **Namal Rajapaksa** | **Dilith Jayaweera** |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| 1. Economic Policy and Growth Strategies | Target $180 billion GDP, expand economic freedom, encourage entrepreneurship | Prioritize investments for entrepreneurial development, promote strategic investments |\n| 2. Education Reform and Innovation | Introduce political education, review and upgrade education syllabi | Establish Sri Lanka Education Index, strengthen free education, introduce national education policy |\n| 3. Energy and Sustainability | Invest in renewable energy, develop Sri Lanka as a regional centre for renewable energy export | Implement national energy efficiency policy, promote renewable energy, develop Sri Lanka as an energy hub |\n| 4. Healthcare System and Public Health | Develop targeted public healthcare facilities, reduce drug prices, promote private hospital services | Introduce national health insurance fund, establish authority to regulate indigenous medical practices |\n| 5. National Security and Defense | Ensure internal security, strengthen constitution, modernize security forces | Implement defense strategy, employ advanced surveillance technology, protect economy from threats |\n| 6. Legal Framework and Judicial Reform | Strengthen constitution, promote democracy, remove regulatory and legal barriers | Expand legal aid services, implement reforms to criminal justice system, establish chapter on duties of citizens |\n| 7. Transportation and Mobility | Improve transport system, invest in housing construction, promote use of railways | Create integrated transport plan, develop scientific mechanism to utilize railway infrastructure, introduce 'circular' bus routes |\n| 8. Infrastructure Development and Modernization | Develop physical and soft infrastructure, invest in airport and seaport development | Develop comprehensive national plan to improve energy efficiency, initiate projects to rehabilitate and develop rural roads |\n| 9. Foreign Policy and International Relations | Pursue equally friendly yet non-aligned foreign policy, promote international cooperation, remove barriers to foreign investment | Adopt flexible, multi-aligned foreign policy, provide continuous training and support to ambassadors, leverage international partnerships |\n\n**Common Policies:**\n\n* Emphasis on economic growth and development\n* Importance of education and healthcare\n* Focus on renewable energy and sustainability\n* Need for a strong and effective governance framework\n\n**Unique/Innovative Policies:**\n\n* Namal Rajapaksa:\n\t+ Development of a \"Creator Economy\"\n\t+ Establishment of a \"Healing Haven\" for advanced healthcare services\n\t+ Museum and library to commemorate the humanitarian war against terrorism\n* Dilith Jayaweera:\n\t+ Establishment of a Sri Lanka Education Index\n\t+ Introduction of a national health insurance fund\n\t+ Development of Sri Lanka as an energy hub\n\n**Analysis:**\n\n* Namal Rajapaksa's policies focus on economic growth, education, healthcare, and national security, with an emphasis on entrepreneurship, innovation, and infrastructure development.\n* Dilith Jayaweera's policies prioritize entrepreneurship, innovation, and strategic investments, with a focus on education, healthcare, and energy sustainability.\n* Both candidates recognize the importance of a strong and effective governance framework to support economic growth and development.\n* Namal Rajapaksa's policies seem to be more focused on specific projects and initiatives, while Dilith Jayaweera's policies appear to be more focused on overall strategies and frameworks."